article.headline: Butler 23, Valparaiso 14
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Ryan Hitchcock ran for two touchdowns Saturday as Butler remained undefeated with a 23-14 win over state rival Valparaiso. Scott Gray carried the other touchdown for Butler (6-0, 3-0 Pioneer Football League) and led the game in rushing with 99 yards. The team's defense had four sacks and held Valparaiso (1-5, 0-3) to 249 yards. Valpo's QBs completed just 8 of 21 passing tries. Eli Crawford made perhaps Valparaiso's biggest play, intercepting a third-quarter pass by Butler's Andrew Huck and returning it 60 yards for the TD. Quinn Schafer ran for the team's other touchdown later in the quarter.
